data.text:
Debt Levels Nokia Corp can leverage the use of borrowed funds to amplify returns from an investment. In general, analyzing the relationship between debt to total assets helps investors to understand Nokia Corp's financial leverage. It provides some insight into what part of Nokia Corp's total assets is financed by creditors. Liquidity Nokia Corp ADR has 5.19 B in debt with debt to equity (D/E) ratio of 0.29, which may show that the company is not taking advantage of profits from borrowing. Nokia Corp ADR has a current ratio of 1.5, which is typical for the industry and considered as normal. Note however, debt could still be an excellent tool for Nokia to invest in growth at high rates of return.
